#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:1
msgid "R-Fork"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:3
msgid ""
"R-Fork (Tensor Remote Fork) is a novel weight loading methodology that "
"leverages efficient inter-node GPU-to-GPU data transfer path to load tensors "
"from a running SGLang instance to a new instance with zero-copy. It can "
"significantly optimize the SGLang instance boot-up time by reducing model "
"weights loading from several minutes to mere seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:5
msgid ""
"To learn more details about R-Fork, please check **<a href=https://lmsys.org/"
"blog/2025-12-10-rfork/> R-Fork blog </a>**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:5
msgid "<a href=https://lmsys.org/blog/2025-12-10-rfork/>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:5
msgid "</a>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0 ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:7
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid "Argument"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid "load-format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid "set to `remote_instance` to enable R-Fork."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid "remote-instance-weight-loader-backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid "`nccl`, `transfer_engine`, or `modelexpress`. Default is `nccl`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid "remote-instance-weight-loader-seed-instance-ip"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid ""
"IP address of the seed instance who will provide the model weight. Used by "
"`nccl` and `transfer_engine` backends."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid "remote-instance-weight-loader-seed-instance-service-port"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid ""
"the port that the seed instance's HTTP server is listening on. Used by "
"`nccl` and `transfer_engine` backends."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid "remote-instance-weight-loader-send-weights-group-ports"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid ""
"the list of available ports on the seed instance that will be used to build "
"NCCL communication groups between seed and client instance. Only needed by "
"`nccl` backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid "remote-instance-weight-loader-start-seed-via-transfer-engine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid ""
"set to start seed service that supports TransferEngine as backend. Needed "
"for seed instances when using `transfer_engine` as backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid "modelexpress-config"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:0
msgid ""
"JSON config for `modelexpress` backend. Keys: `\"url\"` (required, gRPC host:"
"port of ModelExpress server), `\"model_name\"` (optional, defaults to `--"
"model-path`), `\"source\"` (optional bool, `true` for seed mode)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:19
msgid "NCCL as backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:21
#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:38
#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:58
msgid "seed instance:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:22
msgid "python -m sglang.launch_server [args]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:26
#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:64
msgid "client instance:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:27
msgid ""
"python -m sglang.launch_server [args] \\\n"
"  --load-format remote_instance \\\n"
"  --remote-instance-weight-loader-seed-instance-ip [seed_instance_ip] \\\n"
"  --remote-instance-weight-loader-seed-instance-service-port "
"[seed_instance_service_port] \\\n"
"  --remote-instance-weight-loader-send-weights-group-ports "
"[send_weights_nccl_group_ports_list]  \\\n"
"  --remote-instance-weight-loader-backend nccl\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:36
msgid "TransferEngine as backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:39
msgid ""
"python -m sglang.launch_server [args] \\\n"
"  --remote-instance-weight-loader-start-seed-via-transfer-engine\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:44
msgid ""
"python -m sglang.launch_server [args] \\\n"
"  --load-format remote_instance \\\n"
"  --remote-instance-weight-loader-seed-instance-ip [seed_instance_ip] \\\n"
"  --remote-instance-weight-loader-seed-instance-service-port "
"[seed_instance_service_port] \\\n"
"  --remote-instance-weight-loader-backend transfer_engine\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:52
msgid "ModelExpress as backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:54
msgid ""
"[ModelExpress](https://github.com/ai-dynamo/modelexpress) is a coordination "
"service that manages P2P weight transfer metadata. It removes the need for "
"direct seed IP/port configuration by providing a centralized registry that "
"seeds publish to and clients discover from. Under the hood it uses "
"TransferEngine (Mooncake) for the actual RDMA data transfer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:56
msgid ""
"A running ModelExpress server is required. See the [ModelExpress "
"documentation](https://github.com/ai-dynamo/modelexpress) for setup "
"instructions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:59
msgid ""
"python -m sglang.launch_server [args] \\\n"
"  --modelexpress-config '{\"url\": \"[modelexpress_grpc_host:port]\", "
"\"model_name\": \"[model_name]\", \"source\": true}'\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:65
msgid ""
"python -m sglang.launch_server [args] \\\n"
"  --load-format remote_instance \\\n"
"  --remote-instance-weight-loader-backend modelexpress \\\n"
"  --modelexpress-config '{\"url\": \"[modelexpress_grpc_host:port]\", "
"\"model_name\": \"[model_name]\"}'\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/rfork.md:72
msgid ""
"The seed publishes its TransferEngine session ID and tensor layout to "
"ModelExpress. The client queries ModelExpress to discover the seed, then "
"pulls weights directly via RDMA. This enables dynamic seed discovery without "
"hardcoding IPs, and supports multiple models through a single ModelExpress "
"instance."
msgstr ""
